  "instructions": [
    "Roast the red peppers over an open flame or in the oven at 400°F (200°C) for 30-40 minutes, or until the skin is charred and blistered.",
    "Peel the skin off the peppers and chop them into a large bowl.",
    "Add the brined feta cheese, pitted green olives, toasted pine nuts, fresh parsley, fresh lime leaves, garlic, lemon juice, salt, black pepper, and paprika to the bowl with the roasted peppers.",
    "Mix everything together until well combined.",
    "Drizzle the olive oil over the top and mix again until the mixture is smooth and gooey.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes to allow the flavors to meld.",
    "Serve the muhammara chilled, garnished with additional parsley and lime leaves if desired."
  ],
